We now discuss three different responses to the disease outbreak. We assume that neither a vaccine nor effective antiviral drugs become available. We will also assume that the contact numbers can be reduced by discrete values. We assume that the response to the disease started at the point in time when the fraction of the infected population exceeded some threshold value \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
